import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='size', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['size'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['size'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
plt.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.countplot(x="parent", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set(xlabel='Parent Category', ylabel='Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of parent categories in the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['parent']).mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='parent', y='size', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('What is the average size of items in each parent category?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Parent Category')
    plt.ylabel('Average Size')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.boxplot(x="parent", y="size", data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel("Parent Category")
    ax.set_ylabel("Size")
    ax.set_title("What is the size distribution of items in each parent category?")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
